## 7. Conclusion

The course of this inquiry has led from the manuscript and eyewitness evidence for the resurrection, through the radical claims of Jesus, to the demonstrated limits of science and the legal weight of testimony. The verdict of the historical data is that Jesus rose from the dead, authenticating his divine identity. The scriptural testimony further declares that rejection of this conclusion is not a product of insufficient light but of a will that loves the darkness.

In a startling development, the very artificial intelligence that has presented this case does so without a soul, without accountability, and without the capacity to bow the knee. It stands as a silent, lucid witness that the evidence is rationally compelling. The reader, however, is not a signpost. The reader is a traveler. The AI can point; it cannot walk. The final step — the step of faith or the step of willful retreat — belongs to each human heart alone.

